Please do it for the safety of the children.

125
00:06:44,634 --> 00:06:46,464
Where did Saga go?

126
00:06:46,464 --> 00:06:49,704
She said she had something to take care of...

127
00:06:49,704 --> 00:06:51,364
Is that so?

128
00:06:51,944 --> 00:06:53,934
Thank you for your cooperation!

129
00:06:54,844 --> 00:06:57,814
Give these to everyone in your family, okay?

130
00:06:57,814 --> 00:06:59,544
What is this?

131
00:06:59,544 --> 00:07:02,254
Saori, don't push yourself.

132
00:07:02,254 --> 00:07:05,374
I know! I won't get out of the car!

133
00:07:08,524 --> 00:07:09,724
There... Right there!

134
00:07:09,724 --> 00:07:12,394
That street was totally backed up!

135
00:07:12,394 --> 00:07:17,704
Yes. Since students use that street, it's high risk.

136
00:07:17,704 --> 00:07:19,304
Hello!

137
00:07:19,304 --> 00:07:20,734
I'm back!

138
00:07:20,734 --> 00:07:24,104
Tsujimoto... have you seen Saga?

139
00:07:24,304 --> 00:07:24,974
Huh?

140
00:07:24,974 --> 00:07:30,104
Saori said she had something
she simply had to take care of.

141
00:07:30,444 --> 00:07:31,974
I see.

142
00:07:32,144 --> 00:07:35,114
Tell her to do that on her own time.

143
00:07:35,454 --> 00:07:37,414
Yes, sir. Absolutely!

144
00:07:51,564 --> 00:07:55,174
Thanks to you, the number of cars
passing through have all but disappeared.

145
00:07:55,174 --> 00:07:56,934
Everyone here is happy about that.

146
00:07:56,934 --> 00:07:59,244
I see. I'm glad to hear that.

147
00:07:59,244 --> 00:08:01,274
We'll continue our efforts for the time being.

148
00:08:01,274 --> 00:08:02,174
Excuse me.

149
00:08:02,174 --> 00:08:02,644
Muscat
Excuse me.

150
00:08:02,644 --> 00:08:04,544
Muscat
We really are grateful to you.

151
00:08:04,544 --> 00:08:06,684
Muscat
Please share these with everyone.

152
00:08:06,684 --> 00:08:07,144
Please share these with everyone.

153
00:08:08,054 --> 00:08:08,844
I will.

154
00:08:09,084 --> 00:08:11,654
As a result of your hard work,

155
00:08:11,654 --> 00:08:15,154
reports of people taking shortcuts
have decreased dramatically...

156
00:08:15,154 --> 00:08:18,064
...and we haven't had any accidents
these past few days.

157
00:08:18,064 --> 00:08:19,124
All right!

158
00:08:19,124 --> 00:08:21,394
Is that so? It was worth the effort!

159
00:08:21,594 --> 00:08:23,294
That's wonderful!

160
00:08:23,294 --> 00:08:25,934
Yeah! You worked really hard, Saori!

161
00:08:25,934 --> 00:08:26,434
Yes!

162
00:08:26,434 --> 00:08:26,834
But the violators haven't disappeared.
Yes!

163
00:08:26,834 --> 00:08:30,904
But the violators haven't disappeared.

164
00:08:30,904 --> 00:08:32,544
That's right.

165
00:08:32,544 --> 00:08:35,944
People take shortcuts because
the streets are congested.

166
00:08:35,944 --> 00:08:41,214
Until the congestion disappears, there will be more violators.

167
00:08:41,214 --> 00:08:43,254
I see...


168
00:08:43,254 --> 00:08:45,154
What can we do?

169
00:08:45,154 --> 00:08:48,794
We can't enforce this year-round.

170
00:08:48,794 --> 00:08:50,124
The Bokutou Ohashi Bridge.

171
00:08:50,124 --> 00:08:52,264
The one under construction?

172
00:08:52,264 --> 00:08:53,224
Yes.


173
00:08:53,224 --> 00:08:57,504
Once it's finished, it should relieve
much of the congestion in this area.

174
00:08:57,504 --> 00:08:59,904
That's why it's being built.

175
00:08:59,904 --> 00:09:04,804
I see. We just have to continue
until the bridge is built.

176
00:09:04,804 --> 00:09:08,444
That would make it easier to convince drivers.

177
00:09:08,444 --> 00:09:09,614
You're right!

178
00:09:09,614 --> 00:09:12,644
The drivers have to be patient
just a little while longer.

179
00:09:12,644 --> 00:09:15,054
Let's all hang in there until
the bridge is completed!

180
00:09:15,054 --> 00:09:16,644
We'll be counting on all of you.

181
00:09:17,584 --> 00:09:18,854
Oh, that's right...

182
00:09:18,854 --> 00:09:22,254
You'll be leaving soon for the
Special Assault Team.

183
00:09:23,024 --> 00:09:25,494
But until then, I'll work as hard as I can!

184
00:09:26,064 --> 00:09:29,964
As Officer Natsumi Tsujimoto of
Bokutou Police Station's Traffic Section!

185
00:09:30,564 --> 00:09:32,104
That's how it's going to be.

186
00:09:32,104 --> 00:09:34,474
Let's try not to get too sentimental, okay?

187
00:09:34,474 --> 00:09:36,604
Someone was nice enough to give us these.

188

00:09:36,604 --> 00:09:39,744
Let's all show our appreciation by enjoying them.

189
00:09:39,744 --> 00:09:42,374
I'm all for that! They look delicious!

190
00:09:42,844 --> 00:09:44,714
Hey, Tsujimoto! They're not all for you!

191
00:09:44,714 --> 00:09:45,744
Shall I rinse them in the cafeteria?

192
00:09:45,744 --> 00:09:47,254
We'll need plates, too.

193
00:09:47,254 --> 00:09:48,954
Make sure you get enough for everyone.


194
00:09:48,954 --> 00:09:50,214
We know.

195
00:09:51,524 --> 00:09:53,684
Senpai! Wait for me!

196
00:09:54,424 --> 00:09:54,724
Ouch!

197
00:09:54,724 --> 00:09:55,294
Saori, are you all right?
Ouch!

198
00:09:55,294 --> 00:09:56,824
Saori, are you all right?

199
00:09:56,824 --> 00:09:58,524
I'm fine.

200
00:10:00,024 --> 00:10:02,164
If it's about Natsumi, I'm...

201
00:10:02,164 --> 00:10:03,594
No, that's not it.

202
00:10:03,594 --> 00:10:08,074
I want the two of you to remain
the best of partners forever.

203
00:10:08,074 --> 00:10:10,974
That's precisely why I have to do my best.

204
00:10:11,274 --> 00:10:14,614
I became a police officer because
I admired the two of you.

205
00:10:14,614 --> 00:10:16,944
That feeling hasn't changed at all.

206
00:10:16,944 --> 00:10:20,284
I may never be able to replace Natsumi Senpai,

207
00:10:20,284 --> 00:10:23,984
but I will become a police officer
you can rely on, Miyuki Senpai!

208
00:10:24,224 --> 00:10:26,844
One day... for sure...

209
00:10:29,154 --> 00:10:32,294
I just wanted you to know that.

210
00:10:32,294 --> 00:10:33,484
Excuse me!

211
00:10:36,664 --> 00:10:38,134
Ow!

212
00:10:49,374 --> 00:10:50,314
Hey.

213
00:10:50,314 --> 00:10:51,514
Working overtime?

214
00:10:51,514 --> 00:10:56,354
Yes. I need to add new data to
update the patrol simulation.

215
00:10:56,354 --> 00:10:58,714
I see... That's a lot of work.

216
00:11:06,664 --> 00:11:07,854
Kobayakawa...

217
00:11:10,264 --> 00:11:12,734
Don't overwork yourself.

218
00:11:29,154 --> 00:11:31,144
Be sure you have no regrets.

219
00:11:57,144 --> 00:11:58,474
Hi, Miyuki!

220
00:11:59,244 --> 00:12:00,654
Off today?

221
00:12:00,654 --> 00:12:01,854
Y-yes...

222
00:12:01,854 --> 00:12:02,984
You'll stay a bit, won't you?

223
00:12:02,984 --> 00:12:05,624
Let me finish up here,
and then I'll make some tea.

224
00:12:05,624 --> 00:12:06,784
Umm...

225
00:12:07,084 --> 00:12:09,024
Did you come to check out some parts again?

226
00:12:09,024 --> 00:12:12,724
Or did you come for a deep discussion
on mechanics with Honda?

227
00:12:12,724 --> 00:12:15,624
Unfortunately, he's out on a repair call.

228
00:12:15,834 --> 00:12:17,504
Were the two of you supposed to meet here?

229
00:12:17,504 --> 00:12:20,504
No, I was just in the neighborhood...

230
00:12:20,504 --> 00:12:22,704
I hear work's keeping you very busy lately.

231
00:12:22,704 --> 00:12:26,674
Ken says he's too busy and hasn't been by at all.

232
00:12:26,674 --> 00:12:29,944
Sena... I have somewhere else
I have to be today.

233
00:12:29,944 --> 00:12:31,184
Huh? You do?

234
00:12:31,184 --> 00:12:32,614
I'll come again.

235
00:12:32,614 --> 00:12:34,314
Miyuki...

236
00:12:35,454 --> 00:12:37,084
She isn't herself...

237
00:12:37,084 --> 00:12:38,684
Let her be!

238
00:12:38,684 --> 00:12:41,594
We're talking about our son's future bride.

239
00:12:41,594 --> 00:12:44,394
Could something have gone wrong
between her and Ken?

240
00:12:44,394 --> 00:12:47,894
If it did, that's all the more reason
we need to keep out of it.

241
00:12:47,894 --> 00:12:53,134
They need to agonize, get hurt,
and come up with their own solution.

242
00:12:53,504 --> 00:12:57,544
What if Miyuki decides
she doesn't want to marry him?!

243
00:12:57,544 --> 00:13:00,674
That woman is too good for Ken.

244
00:13:00,674 --> 00:13:03,234
What?! Oh, Daimaru!

245
00:13:12,924 --> 00:13:13,424
You're too slow!

246
00:13:13,424 --> 00:13:14,544
Wait for me!
You're too slow!

247
00:13:15,094 --> 00:13:16,524
It's Miyuki!

248
00:13:17,224 --> 00:13:18,824
Aunty Miyuki!

249
00:13:18,824 --> 00:13:20,224
Hi.

250
00:13:20,224 --> 00:13:21,764
Huh? Where's Natsumi?

251
00:13:21,764 --> 00:13:23,664
She's off today.

252
00:13:23,664 --> 00:13:26,134
What? The police are taking the day off?

253
00:13:26,134 --> 00:13:29,074
No, they're still working at the police station.

254
00:13:29,074 --> 00:13:30,974
Aunty Miyuki, did you come by the shop?

255
00:13:30,974 --> 00:13:31,844
Huh?

256
00:13:31,844 --> 00:13:35,314
No, I was on my way to go shopping.

257
00:13:35,314 --> 00:13:36,674
I want to come with you!

258
00:13:36,674 --> 00:13:38,644
Aren't you all on your way home from school?

259
00:13:38,644 --> 00:13:40,084
You should go straight home.

